		<h1 class="h1">How to install C</h1>
		<p>
			There are many compilers available for c and c++. You need to
			download any one. Here, we are going to use <strong>Turbo
				C++</strong>. It will work for both C and C++. To install the Turbo C
			software, you need to follow following steps.
		</p>
		<ol class="points">
			<li>Download Turbo C++</li>
			<li>Create turboc directory inside c drive and extract the
				tc3.zip inside c:\turboc</li>
			<li>Double click on install.exe file</li>
			<li>Click on the tc application file located inside c:\TC\BIN to
				write the c program</li>
		</ol>
		<h2 class="h3">1) Download Turbo C++ software</h2>
		<p>
			You can download turbo c++ from many sites. <a
				href="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/software/tc3.zip">download
				Turbo c++</a>
		</p>
		<h2 class="h3">2) Create turboc directory in c drive and extract
			the tc3.zip</h2>
		<p>Now, you need to create a new directory turboc inside the c:
			drive. Now extract the tc3.zip file in c:\truboc directory.</p>
		<h2 class="h3">3) Double click on the install.exe file and follow
			steps</h2>
		<p>Now, click on the install icon located inside the c:\turboc</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc1.jpg"
			width="700" alt="install turbo c++" />
		<p>It will ask you to install c or not, press enter to install.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc2.jpg"
			alt="how to install  turbo c++" />
		<p>Change your drive to c, press c.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc3.jpg"
			alt="how to install turbo c" />
		<p>Press enter, it will look inside the c:\turboc directory for
			the required files.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc4.jpg"
			alt="how to install turbo c++" />
		<p>Select Start installation by the down arrow key then press
			enter.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc5.jpg"
			alt="how to install turbo c" />
		<p>
			Now C is installed, press enter to read documentation or close the
			software. <img
				src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc6.jpg"
				alt="how to install turbo c" />
		<h2 class="h3">4) Click on the tc application located inside
			c:\TC\BIN</h2>
		<p>Now double click on the tc icon located in c:\TC\BIN directory
			to write the c program.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc7.jpg"
			width="700" alt="tc" />
		<p>In windows 7 or window 8, it will show a dialog block to ignore
			and close the application because fullscreen mode is not supported.
			Click on Ignore button.</p>
		<p>Now it will showing following console.</p>
		<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/cpages/images/installc8.jpg"
